      • from16

        public static UUID from16(byte[] data)
        Create a UUID instance from 16-bit UUID data (little endian).

        This method is an alias of from16(data, 0).

        Parameters:
        data - A byte array containing 16-bit UUID data.
        Returns:
        A UUID instance. null is returned when data is null or offset is not valid.

      • from16

        public static UUID from16(byte[] data,
                          int offset)
        Create a UUID instance from 16-bit UUID data (little endian).

        This method is an alias of from16(data, offset, true).

        Parameters:
        data - A byte array containing 16-bit UUID data.
        offset - The offset from which 16-bit UUID data should be read.
        Returns:
        A UUID instance. null is returned when data is null or offset is not valid.

      • from16

        public static UUID from16(byte[] data,
                          int offset,
                          boolean littleEndian)
        Create a UUID instance from 16-bit UUID data. 
         // Prepare a byte array containing 32-bit UUID data (little endian).
 byte[] data = new byte[] { (byte)0xAB, (byte)0xCD };

 // Create a UUID instance from the byte array.
 UUID uuid = UUIDCreator.from16(data, 0, true);

 // uuid represents 0000cdab-0000-1000-8000-00805f9b34fb.
        Parameters:
        data - A byte array containing 16-bit UUID data.
        offset - The offset from which 16-bit UUID data should be read.
        littleEndian - true if the 16-bit UUID data is stored in little endian.
        Returns:
        A UUID instance. null is returned when data is null or offset is not valid.

      • from32

        public static UUID from32(byte[] data,
                          int offset,
                          boolean littleEndian)
        Create a UUID instance from 32-bit UUID data. 
         // Prepare a byte array containing 32-bit UUID data (little endian).
 byte[] data = new byte[] { (byte)0x89, (byte)0xAB, (byte)0xCD, (byte)0xEF };

 // Create a UUID instance from the byte array.
 UUID uuid = UUIDCreator.from32(data, 0, true);

 // uuid represents efcdab89-0000-1000-8000-00805f9b34fb.
        Parameters:
        data - A byte array containing 32-bit UUID data.
        offset - The offset from which 32-bit UUID data should be read.
        littleEndian - true if the 32-bit UUID data is stored in little endian.
        Returns:
        A UUID instance. null is returned when data is null or offset is not valid.

      • from128

        public static UUID from128(byte[] data,
                           int offset)
        Create a UUID instance from 128-bit UUID data. 
         // Prepare a byte array containing 128-bit UUID data (little endian).
 byte[] data = new byte[] {
     (byte)0x01, (byte)0x23, (byte)0x45, (byte)0x67,
     (byte)0x89, (byte)0xAB, (byte)0xCD, (byte)0xEF,
     (byte)0xFE, (byte)0xDC, (byte)0xBA, (byte)0x98,
     (byte)0x76, (byte)0x54, (byte)0x32, (byte)0x10 };

 // Create a UUID instance from the byte array.
 UUID uuid = UUIDCreator.from32(data, 0, true);

 // uuid represents 01234567-89ab-cdef-fedc-ba9876543210.
        Parameters:
        data - A byte array containing 128-bit UUID data.
        offset - The offset from which 128-bit UUID data should be read.
        Returns:
        A UUID instance. null is returned when data is null or offset is not valid.
